<item>
            <title>[SPARK-9437] SizeEstimator overflows for primitive arrays</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-9437</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;SizeEstimator&lt;/tt&gt; can overflow when dealing w/ large primitive arrays eg if you have an &lt;tt&gt;Array&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Double&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt; of size 1 &amp;lt;&amp;lt; 28.  This means that when you try to broadcast a large primitive array, you get:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: requirement failed: sizeInBytes was negative: -2147483608
   at scala.Predef$.require(Predef.scala:233)
   at org.apache.spark.storage.BlockInfo.markReady(BlockInfo.scala:55)
   at org.apache.spark.storage.BlockManager.doPut(BlockManager.scala:815)
   at org.apache.spark.storage.BlockManager.putIterator(BlockManager.scala:638)
...
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
